WEBVTT

00:02.228 --> 00:04.319
And finally, this year's
most powerful woman

00:04.338 --> 00:07.581
in business, Paula Clark.

00:07.733 --> 00:09.416
<i> (soft music)</i>

00:09.510 --> 00:12.177
-The Executioner.
-PAULA: Thank you for this.

00:12.370 --> 00:15.347
I'm often asked how to have
a successful career

00:15.499 --> 00:18.517
as a woman in this industry,
and the first thing I'd say is,

00:18.668 --> 00:21.353
forget everything you know
about being a woman.

00:21.505 --> 00:25.507
The companies that survive
in a ruthless marketplace

00:25.601 --> 00:29.269
are the efficient ones,
not the nice ones.

00:29.363 --> 00:32.197
Inefficiency is the tumor
you need to excise,

00:32.349 --> 00:34.015
in order to save the rest.

00:34.035 --> 00:36.201
And yes, sometimes
that means layoffs,

00:36.370 --> 00:41.098
but business is
about hard decisions.

00:41.116 --> 00:43.709
I know that some people call me
The Executioner.

00:43.860 --> 00:45.377
That's not accurate.

00:45.604 --> 00:51.608
I'm a surgeon, and when I do
my job, the patient thrives.

00:51.627 --> 00:52.943
Thank you.

00:52.961 --> 00:59.224
(applause)

01:01.453 --> 01:04.805
Call my job a tumor again,
you corporate rat!

01:04.899 --> 01:07.733
<i> (upbeat music)</i>

01:07.960 --> 01:09.551
<i> ♪ </i>

01:09.570 --> 01:12.237
All right, is everybody here?
Where's Monica?

01:12.389 --> 01:17.725
<i> ♪ </i>

01:17.745 --> 01:18.985
Don't say anything.

01:19.138 --> 01:22.247
About what?
Oh, about the cane?

01:22.474 --> 01:23.974
Think that's what
you're talking about, the cane.

01:24.067 --> 01:26.143
A lot of people
use canes, Monica.

01:26.236 --> 01:27.661
Winston Churchill had a cane.

01:27.813 --> 01:28.995
Scrooge McDuck, Willy Wonka.

01:29.090 --> 01:30.647
-Charlie Chaplin.
-Hugh Laurie,<i> House.</i>

01:30.666 --> 01:32.833
-Hit show, that was a hit show.
-Oh, good, good.

01:32.985 --> 01:34.075
-He was good, right?
-So hot.

01:34.169 --> 01:35.168
-That acting.
-So hot!

01:35.321 --> 01:37.321
-DANTE: So ripped.
-Ripped?

01:37.339 --> 01:39.506
-I hate all of you.
-So the deal for today.

01:39.600 --> 01:41.508
Jessica and Dante are gonna be
taking half the cast off site.

01:41.602 --> 01:44.103
This is a heartwarming
background package.

01:44.254 --> 01:46.271
I want nostalgia, I want
tearful high school memories,

01:46.498 --> 01:47.422
I want a nap just thinking
about it,

01:47.441 --> 01:49.090
but, guys,
we gotta make it pop.

01:49.168 --> 01:50.792
That's about it--the rest
of us are gonna be here.

01:50.853 --> 01:52.594
Monica, you can lead rehearsal,
and try not to take out any

01:52.613 --> 01:53.837
knees or eyes with that thing.

01:53.930 --> 01:55.172
Should be an easy day, guys.
Let's get to it.

01:55.190 --> 01:56.506
Nick, a word?

01:56.525 --> 01:58.175
Alan, we just
letting 'em in now?

01:58.193 --> 02:00.953
Is that what's happening?

02:01.180 --> 02:03.122
Hey, all right.

02:03.349 --> 02:06.183
Here, you know what?
Have a seat, please.

02:06.201 --> 02:09.035
I've recently learned
some concerning information

02:09.130 --> 02:11.296
about my employment history

02:11.448 --> 02:13.114
vis-à-vis Mike's
employment history.

02:13.134 --> 02:15.542
-Oh, yeah, what's that?
-I know you already know.

02:15.694 --> 02:20.364
I do, The Executioner.
Hoo-hoo, I'm shaking.

02:20.382 --> 02:22.032
I want to be the one
to tell him in person.

02:22.050 --> 02:23.291
Sure, of course.

02:23.310 --> 02:24.810
I'll set up an SDI
for the two of you guys today.

02:24.961 --> 02:26.311
No.

02:26.463 --> 02:28.480
I want to tell him off-camera
before I tell him on-camera.

02:28.707 --> 02:30.149
No, come on, no can do.
You signed a contract.

02:30.300 --> 02:32.709
We get to film anything
and everything deemed important

02:32.728 --> 02:35.045
to the<i> Big Leap</i> story,
and this is very important.

02:35.138 --> 02:38.806
Right, okay.
That makes sense.

02:38.826 --> 02:40.141
I agree.

02:40.235 --> 02:44.404
Oh, we got a runner!
Make a V formation!

02:44.498 --> 02:45.980
-STAFFER: What is that?
-ALLY: Cut her off!

02:46.000 --> 02:47.557
-Mike!
-NICK: Cut her off!

02:47.576 --> 02:49.743
Don't do this.
We can talk about it!

02:49.895 --> 02:51.912
-Paula.
-Mike!

02:52.047 --> 02:52.913
ALLY: Are you serious
right now?

02:53.007 --> 02:54.231
I'm not running.

02:54.249 --> 02:55.465
I have off-brand shoes.

02:57.661 --> 02:59.178
Nice, Ally.

02:59.329 --> 03:00.921
Hey, make sure you take
her phone.

03:01.089 --> 03:02.239
She is on hard ice
from now on.

03:02.332 --> 03:03.849
Hey, anybody got eyes on Mike?

03:04.000 --> 03:06.259
MIKE: Oh, love cottage cheese.

03:06.353 --> 03:10.096
It's like my favorite cheese,
which I know is weird,

03:10.249 --> 03:13.583
but, like,
it's not just for babies--oof!

03:13.677 --> 03:17.863
You look extra bulgy today.
Is that for me?

03:18.090 --> 03:19.347
I just ramped up my workouts.

03:19.441 --> 03:20.866
You know, trying to get back
in football shape.

03:21.093 --> 03:22.275
BRITTNEY: Well, I like it.

03:22.369 --> 03:25.429
Mm, just want to show you off.
(gasps)

03:25.447 --> 03:27.021
We should go to Tulum
next year.

03:27.190 --> 03:29.115
-Next year?
-Yeah.

03:29.210 --> 03:30.600
Between filming
and your football season,

03:30.619 --> 03:33.770
we won't be able to leave
till, what, February?

03:33.863 --> 03:36.440
But that's okay.

03:36.458 --> 03:39.534
-Gabby, you're staring.
-Sorry, sorry.

03:39.553 --> 03:42.537
It's just that he hasn't,
you know, acknowledged

03:42.706 --> 03:46.541
what I said the other day
about him, and love, and me.

03:46.560 --> 03:49.377
Yeah, maybe he's just
processing all that,

03:49.504 --> 03:53.381
but who cares?
Because you're famous.

03:53.400 --> 03:55.308
Hey, did they tell you
what we're doing today?

03:55.402 --> 03:57.569
'Cause this is
our neighborhood.

03:57.721 --> 03:59.980
<i> GABBY: No--wait.</i>

04:00.132 --> 04:04.134
BOTH: Oh, no.

04:04.227 --> 04:07.988
We're going back
to high school.

04:08.156 --> 04:10.974
This is fun, huh?
It's cute.

04:11.067 --> 04:13.827
-Oh, for who?
-Here.

04:13.963 --> 04:16.162
Welcome,
theater and art students.

04:16.315 --> 04:19.165
We have some very special
guests for you today.

04:19.318 --> 04:20.333
-What are we doing here?
-Background package.

04:20.486 --> 04:21.927
You're gonna meet
with your old dance team,

04:22.078 --> 04:23.320
teach them
your state-winning dance,

04:23.413 --> 04:25.246
do some interviews,
some B-roll,

04:25.266 --> 04:27.991
and give them this giant check,
easy-peasy.

04:28.084 --> 04:29.268
PRINCIPAL:
Put your hands together

04:29.495 --> 04:32.938
for Justin Calgrove
and Gabby Lewis!

04:33.165 --> 04:35.165
-Ooh!
-JESSICA: Get out there.

04:35.183 --> 04:37.501
-PRINCIPAL: 10,000
-SIMON: Really?

04:37.594 --> 04:39.761
Oh.

04:39.780 --> 04:45.951
Um... as distinguished alumni,
it is our pleasure to be able

04:46.120 --> 04:48.620
to give you
this huge-ass check.

04:50.032 --> 04:53.350
Oh, it's--it's very surprising
to be here.

04:53.368 --> 04:54.776
Wouldn't have minded
a heads-up,

04:54.870 --> 04:58.446
but follow your dreams.

04:58.540 --> 05:02.283
You know, we did, and we're now
on a dance TV show, so...

05:02.377 --> 05:04.118
Doesn't that guy work
at the bowling alley?

05:04.138 --> 05:06.029
Hey, I quit that job
three weeks ago.

05:06.048 --> 05:07.288
We'll cut that out.

05:07.308 --> 05:08.640
Once again,
it's Gabby, Gabby, Gabby.

05:08.867 --> 05:11.476
Brittney, this is literally
her background package.

05:11.645 --> 05:12.369
Zip it.

05:12.538 --> 05:13.478
I'm just saying these kids

05:13.630 --> 05:16.540
deserve a real role model,
like Reggie.

05:16.708 --> 05:18.817
You should be out there,
instead of these losers.

05:18.968 --> 05:20.560
They're not losers.

05:20.712 --> 05:22.045
Yeah, actually, Reggie,
that's a good idea.

05:22.064 --> 05:23.547
Why don't you go talk
about success?

05:23.565 --> 05:24.881
-Yes.
-What, wait.

05:24.900 --> 05:25.882
Go, babe, go, go.

05:25.901 --> 05:27.475
Go, go, get out there.

05:27.494 --> 05:29.644
-SIMON: Here is Reggie.
-GABBY: Oh, great.

05:29.721 --> 05:33.890
♪

05:33.909 --> 05:36.335
Hey, hi, I'm Reggie Sadler.

05:36.562 --> 05:39.245
Whoo!

05:39.398 --> 05:42.232
I'm a football player,
as many of you know,

05:42.325 --> 05:46.086
and, uh, the way
that I achieved my dreams

05:46.238 --> 05:48.738
was through focus, you know?

05:48.757 --> 05:51.925
So there's a lot
of distractions in the world,

05:52.077 --> 05:53.518
so you know, eyes on the prize.

05:53.670 --> 05:57.338
You know, for me,
that prize was football.

05:57.432 --> 06:01.342
Is football.
Still is football.

06:01.436 --> 06:03.695
You know, in fact,
I need to lead by example.

06:03.847 --> 06:05.939
-Brittney?
-Yeah, babe?

06:06.091 --> 06:07.090
Look, I'm--I'm sorry,
but we're done.

06:07.259 --> 06:10.110
-What, babe?
-It's over.

06:10.262 --> 06:11.928
You know,
I can't do this anymore.

06:12.097 --> 06:14.097
I gotta focus, you know?

06:14.116 --> 06:15.523
Look, it's not you.
It's me.

06:15.542 --> 06:17.358
Well, I mean, actually,
it's football.

06:17.436 --> 06:19.769
Well, it's me and football,
but it's not you.

06:19.863 --> 06:22.547
-It's not me.
-Not you.

06:22.699 --> 06:25.291
It's not me.

06:25.444 --> 06:28.720
(sobs)
I'm gonna miss him so much.

06:28.872 --> 06:30.371
(sobbing)

06:30.465 --> 06:34.976
Like, I think I loved him,
you know?

06:36.788 --> 06:41.307
All right, thanks, Brittney.
I think we have enough.

06:41.460 --> 06:43.402
Okay, do you need, like,
another color?

06:43.629 --> 06:46.220
'Cause I can do one that's,
like, ragey, you know?

06:46.240 --> 06:48.965
Like...

06:49.058 --> 06:51.743
Reggie Sadler
doesn't deserve me,

06:51.895 --> 06:55.972
but he does deserve revenge.

06:56.065 --> 06:58.308
-It's okay?
-That's great.

06:58.326 --> 07:00.234
Okay.

07:00.254 --> 07:02.646
<i> (DJ Khaled's</i>
<i> "All I Do Is Win")</i>

07:02.664 --> 07:06.073
Yeah, whoo!

07:06.093 --> 07:08.093
Yes.
This is crazy.

07:08.320 --> 07:10.128
This song's bringing back
so many sense memories.

07:10.280 --> 07:13.098
It's like I can almost smell
the White Castle and hairspray.

07:13.249 --> 07:15.100
God, Gabby, remember?

07:15.327 --> 07:16.843
A little too well, yeah.

07:16.995 --> 07:20.605
<i> ♪ </i>

07:20.757 --> 07:22.256
Hey, Gab.

07:22.276 --> 07:26.336
You see I broke things off
with Brittney today, right?

07:26.354 --> 07:30.932
Yeah, yeah, congrats.
Focusing on football, right?

07:30.951 --> 07:33.843
Yeah, right.

07:33.862 --> 07:37.030
<i> SINGER: ♪ All I do is win,</i>
<i> win, win no matter what ♪</i>

07:37.182 --> 07:40.183
Okay, um...

07:40.202 --> 07:44.037
Guess I'ma catch you later.

07:44.189 --> 07:48.191
<i> SINGER: ♪ Hands go up,</i>
<i> and they stay there ♪</i>

07:48.210 --> 07:51.711
<i> ♪ And they stay there,</i>
<i> and they stay there ♪</i>

07:51.863 --> 07:53.379
Hey, Gabby, you okay?

07:53.532 --> 07:55.699
You've been acting weird
ever since we got here.

07:55.717 --> 07:56.716
Yeah, you know what?

07:56.868 --> 07:58.459
Why are we focusing
on the past?

07:58.553 --> 08:01.295
No one wants to do
the same thing again, anyway.

08:01.315 --> 08:02.889
Let's do something different.

08:03.041 --> 08:04.708
Hunter, right?
Yeah.

08:04.726 --> 08:07.510
Mmm, so good.

08:07.512 --> 08:12.382
-So, Al--can I call you Al?
-Sure.

08:12.400 --> 08:14.067
What's up?
First, you tackle me.

08:14.219 --> 08:15.827
Then we're just sitting
at your desk all day.

08:15.996 --> 08:17.237
Is this a date?

08:17.331 --> 08:19.239
'Cause if it is,
I'm seeing somebody, you know?

08:19.333 --> 08:21.725
Not to brag,
but it's going pretty good.

08:21.893 --> 08:23.243
Good, yeah.

08:23.395 --> 08:25.895
We just have something planned
for you later today, so--

08:25.914 --> 08:28.006
A surprise?

08:28.157 --> 08:31.843
I love surprises.
Not everybody does, but yeah.

08:31.995 --> 08:33.345
No, I love surprises.
It's gonna be good.

08:33.572 --> 08:37.090
Well, it'll certainly be
a surprise.

08:37.242 --> 08:39.500
-Didn't love that tone.
-Sorry.

08:39.594 --> 08:41.077
A little ominous.

08:41.096 --> 08:43.747
Nice shoes.

08:43.840 --> 08:44.931
Stylish and comfortable.

08:45.083 --> 08:46.858
Thanks.

08:47.010 --> 08:49.102
You guys work what,
a 12-hour day?

08:49.254 --> 08:50.770
-More.
-Wow.

08:50.922 --> 08:52.088
ALLY: Mm-hmm.

08:52.181 --> 08:54.107
And I see you.
You're so good at your job.

08:54.259 --> 08:55.275
Does Nick ever tell you that?

08:55.427 --> 08:57.369
I'm not letting you
talk to Mike, Paula.

08:57.596 --> 08:59.204
Okay.

08:59.431 --> 09:03.024
Okay, $500, $1,000.
What's it gonna take?

09:03.118 --> 09:05.435
It's not gonna happen.
God.

09:05.453 --> 09:06.603
Can anyone hear me?

09:06.621 --> 09:08.195
Can anyone hear me?
Can anyone hear me?

09:08.215 --> 09:10.382
-Can anyone hear me?
-It's not on.

09:15.038 --> 09:16.629
Mike!

09:16.723 --> 09:19.115
Mike Devries!

09:19.134 --> 09:22.285
Okay, so here we go.
Five, six, seven, eight.

09:22.304 --> 09:24.954
And one, two, three, four,

09:24.973 --> 09:27.715
five, six, seven, eight,
and one!

09:27.734 --> 09:29.216
This is so good.

09:29.236 --> 09:31.311
I mean, I've never seen you
choreograph anything like this.

09:31.405 --> 09:32.553
Where is it coming from?

09:32.722 --> 09:35.073
I don't know.
Just trusting my gut, I guess.

09:35.300 --> 09:37.075
Gabby, can I steal you

09:37.226 --> 09:39.727
for a quick interview
with your English teacher?

09:39.896 --> 09:42.247
Say hey to Mr. A. for me.

09:42.324 --> 09:44.583
I always knew Gabby
was the one doing all the work

09:44.734 --> 09:48.903
in the group projects,
but she would never admit it.

09:48.997 --> 09:50.589
She was so smart, yes,

09:50.740 --> 09:54.500
but also loyal,
kind, thoughtful.

09:54.595 --> 09:58.488
I'm not at all surprised
to see her here doing this.

09:58.506 --> 10:01.266
Gabby, anything you want to say
to your favorite teacher?

10:05.922 --> 10:07.997
Thank you
for saying all that.

10:08.166 --> 10:11.759
Everyone always loved you,
including me.

10:11.853 --> 10:15.171
You were a great teacher.

10:15.190 --> 10:17.841
Okay, that's great.
Thank you, guys.

10:17.934 --> 10:20.785
We got it.

10:20.937 --> 10:22.512
(whispering)
Keep the camera rolling.

10:22.530 --> 10:24.013
Curtis?

10:24.032 --> 10:25.123
You could have
given me some notice.

10:25.274 --> 10:28.293
I'm sorry.
I didn't know we were coming.

10:28.520 --> 10:30.444
Zach, Zach, my man, listen.
I know you want feel-good.

10:30.538 --> 10:33.523
Trust me, this is going
to be feel-good, all right?

10:33.541 --> 10:34.949
I've never felt so good
in my life.

10:34.968 --> 10:37.118
Yeah.

10:37.137 --> 10:39.804
Nothing.
Yeah, I hear you.

10:40.031 --> 10:41.214
<i> GABBY: Curtis?</i>

10:41.366 --> 10:44.434
<i> MR. ALDERLUND:</i>
<i> He's not here, is he?</i>

10:46.388 --> 10:47.203
<i>No.</i>

10:47.296 --> 10:48.963
Zach.
Yeah, listen, buddy.

10:49.132 --> 10:50.874
I'm gonna have
to call you back.

10:50.967 --> 10:53.376
<i> (soft music)</i>

10:53.395 --> 10:56.655
That's him.
That's the dad.

10:56.882 --> 11:01.567
<i> ♪ </i>

11:01.662 --> 11:03.244
Oh, God, that's the dad.

11:07.150 --> 11:10.393
<i> (upbeat percussion music)</i>

11:10.412 --> 11:12.729
Okay, so today just became
a whole 'nother thing.

11:12.747 --> 11:15.081
Mike is in the van with me.
Paula's coming separately.

11:15.233 --> 11:17.158
Do not let them
within earshot of one another.

11:17.252 --> 11:18.918
We'll do their interview
here later, but first,

11:19.070 --> 11:20.086
I gotta talk to Gabby.
Where is she?

11:20.180 --> 11:22.180
-Right over here.
-All right.

11:22.331 --> 11:24.265
<i> ♪ </i>

11:26.077 --> 11:27.744
You set me up,
you son of a bitch.

11:27.762 --> 11:29.336
Gabby, I had no idea.

11:29.431 --> 11:32.415
It was supposed to be good,
clean fun.

11:32.508 --> 11:35.860
What exactly are we talking
about here, anyway?

11:36.087 --> 11:38.755
I was 18.
I was obsessed with him.

11:38.773 --> 11:40.198
He said he loved me.

11:40.349 --> 11:41.607
When I got pregnant,

11:41.851 --> 11:45.428
he didn't want to have anything
to do with me after that.

11:45.447 --> 11:47.597
So how's that
for good, clean fun?

11:47.766 --> 11:50.858
Man, okay.

11:50.877 --> 11:54.120
-Okay, I'm so sorry, Gabby.
-Are you gonna put this on TV?

11:54.214 --> 11:55.696
I haven't decided yet.

11:55.774 --> 11:57.440
I'm not sure how America's
gonna feel about you.

11:57.533 --> 11:59.959
-Oh, screw you--(gasps)--you.
-Okay, all right.

12:00.053 --> 12:01.219
You know what?
I didn't come on this show

12:01.446 --> 12:03.129
to be the girl who hooked up
with her teacher.

12:03.281 --> 12:05.131
-I quit.
-No, don't quit!

12:05.283 --> 12:06.891
Damn it, come on.
Look, take a walk.

12:07.043 --> 12:08.542
Clear your head.
Just come back

12:08.562 --> 12:11.454
when you're ready.

12:11.473 --> 12:13.214
Jessica?

12:13.233 --> 12:15.641
I need an empty classroom
and all hands on deck.

12:15.794 --> 12:18.628
<i> (heavy hip-hop music)</i>

12:18.721 --> 12:19.963
<i> ♪ </i>

12:20.056 --> 12:21.130
<i> SINGER: ♪ Get it, get it,</i>
<i> get it, uh ♪</i>

12:21.149 --> 12:22.574
<i> ♪ Get it, get it, uh </i>

12:22.801 --> 12:23.891
Yo, that's crazy.

12:23.910 --> 12:25.910
This school
got a Reggie Sadler, too.

12:26.062 --> 12:27.320
Cut.

12:27.472 --> 12:29.138
That's a prop trophy.
These are all props.

12:29.157 --> 12:30.656
We're gonna play this B-roll
over your interview

12:30.809 --> 12:33.142
where you talk about being
a high school football player,

12:33.161 --> 12:34.919
so let that wash over you
or whatever.

12:35.146 --> 12:37.313
-And let's go back to one.
-Okay.

12:37.406 --> 12:38.590
-MAN: Card's full.
-My bad.

12:38.666 --> 12:41.075
Okay, stand by, everyone.
Camera's reloading.

12:41.094 --> 12:43.595
(sighs) Right.

12:43.746 --> 12:46.672
Just need a wash, and...

12:46.767 --> 12:48.099
Hi, Mr. Sadler.

12:48.326 --> 12:50.084
I saw your speech today.

12:50.103 --> 12:53.146
You said I should focus
on my dreams.

12:54.516 --> 12:57.258
My dream is to go to homecoming
with Zoe Washington,

12:57.335 --> 13:00.094
and I was wondering if you
would ask her to go with me.

13:00.188 --> 13:01.613
Wait, so you want me
to ask a girl

13:01.764 --> 13:03.597
to go to homecoming for you?

13:03.617 --> 13:04.857
Yes.

13:05.010 --> 13:06.359
Okay, cool.

13:06.528 --> 13:08.453
Hi, I'm sorry to interrupt.
I couldn't help but overhear,

13:08.622 --> 13:10.288
but now that I've overheard,
I need to insert myself

13:10.515 --> 13:14.775
into this huge mistake
you're making...

13:14.869 --> 13:17.203
-Evan.
-Evan, hi, Evan.

13:17.297 --> 13:19.113
Now, did you see the way
that this man broke up

13:19.282 --> 13:20.873
with my sister this morning?

13:20.967 --> 13:22.358
Messy.
Tell me.

13:22.451 --> 13:24.710
What does Zoe Washington love
with all of her soul?

13:24.863 --> 13:26.805
Is it the Detroit Lions?

13:27.032 --> 13:28.289
EVAN: I-I don't think so.

13:28.308 --> 13:30.199
Yeah, no.
That's what I thought.

13:30.218 --> 13:31.142
Oh, my God.
You're so lucky I'm here.

13:31.294 --> 13:32.510
Listen, we have limited time,

13:32.662 --> 13:34.203
so it's not gonna be
my best work, but--

13:34.297 --> 13:35.388
Look, man, I'm sorry
for the way

13:35.482 --> 13:37.390
things ended
with your sister, okay?

13:37.466 --> 13:38.817
-Don't be, she's psycho.
-Yeah.

13:38.968 --> 13:39.984
Hey, don't you dare
agree with me.

13:40.211 --> 13:41.711
Evan, don't worry.
I got you.

13:41.729 --> 13:43.062
<i> (line trilling)</i>

13:43.139 --> 13:44.847
-Hey, who are you calling?
-My dove guy.

13:44.899 --> 13:46.140
He owes me.

13:46.234 --> 13:50.053
<i> -DOVE GUY: Hello?</i>
-Hi, guess who?

13:50.055 --> 13:51.220
LINUS: Julia.

13:51.239 --> 13:53.814
Hey, your lav mike is rustling.

13:53.834 --> 13:55.500
Do you mind if I adjust it?

13:55.651 --> 13:56.742
Yeah, sure.

13:56.895 --> 13:58.670
Okay.

13:58.821 --> 14:01.488
Hey, I happened to hear earlier

14:01.583 --> 14:03.991
that you were selling
a classic guitar.

14:04.085 --> 14:05.343
Yeah, yeah I am.

14:05.494 --> 14:07.920
Yeah, sorry.
I hear lots of things.

14:08.073 --> 14:10.256
Well, it's apparently
a 1970s "Lay" Paul--

14:10.408 --> 14:12.075
Les Paul?
Les Paul?

14:12.168 --> 14:14.168
Yeah, you interested?

14:14.187 --> 14:15.520
Yeah, wow, really interested.

14:15.747 --> 14:17.021
Cool, all right.

14:17.173 --> 14:18.523
My daughters are coming in
for an interview

14:18.674 --> 14:19.858
later on this afternoon.

14:20.009 --> 14:21.100
I can ask them to bring it
if you want to see it.

14:21.269 --> 14:24.103
-I would love that.
-Cool, all right, thanks.

14:24.255 --> 14:27.090
Hey, Al.
Why are we in a high school?

14:27.092 --> 14:29.275
And why am I
still in isolation?

14:29.427 --> 14:31.202
Starting to feel like
quarantine all over again,

14:31.371 --> 14:35.206
except, you know, I'm finally
wearing pants, right?

14:35.433 --> 14:38.117
Oh, my God.
Look how precious this is.

14:38.269 --> 14:41.028
Can you believe that?
Love.

14:41.122 --> 14:44.215
Is there anything
sweeter than love?

14:44.367 --> 14:47.218
Yeah.
You ever been in love, Al?

14:47.445 --> 14:50.338
No, but I've thought
about it many a time.

14:50.448 --> 14:53.040
It's out there
waiting for you.

14:53.134 --> 14:54.875
You know what I'm gonna do?

14:54.895 --> 14:57.286
I'm gonna make something
for Paula.

14:57.288 --> 14:59.305
-Oh.
-Yeah, you know?

14:59.457 --> 15:01.215
-Yeah, I don't know.
-Come on.

15:01.234 --> 15:04.235
You know, something that shows
her that I care about her.

15:04.462 --> 15:07.721
Are you sure?
We could do anything else.

15:07.741 --> 15:09.632
I've never been more sure
about anything

15:09.725 --> 15:11.326
in my entire life.

15:15.749 --> 15:17.749
Hey, Gabby?

15:23.164 --> 15:25.298
I think those are
already clean, buddy.

15:28.595 --> 15:31.003
Hey.

15:31.156 --> 15:33.932
<i> (melancholy music)</i>

15:34.083 --> 15:40.680
<i> ♪ </i>

15:40.774 --> 15:43.516
-Nick told you?
-Yeah.

15:43.668 --> 15:45.944
He thought maybe you could use
a friend right now.

15:46.095 --> 15:48.112
<i> ♪ </i>

15:48.264 --> 15:51.265
Mr. A.
I can't believe it.

15:51.284 --> 15:54.101
<i> ♪ </i>

15:54.120 --> 15:56.770
What happened?

15:56.790 --> 16:00.107
I mean, if you want to tell me.

16:00.201 --> 16:02.518
Remember that trip
to Fringe Festival in Montreal?

16:02.611 --> 16:06.706
The one where Clara Draper
got her One Direction tattoo?

16:06.800 --> 16:09.450
<i> ♪ </i>

16:09.469 --> 16:10.951
Yeah.

16:11.045 --> 16:15.381
<i> ♪ </i>

16:15.458 --> 16:17.550
That's the trip
when it started.

16:17.702 --> 16:20.219
<i> ♪ </i>

16:20.371 --> 16:22.963
We were in his room
talking about plays,

16:23.057 --> 16:26.058
and he said
all the right things,

16:26.211 --> 16:28.728
that I was smart,
and valuable, and beautiful.

16:28.822 --> 16:29.970
You are beautiful.

16:30.048 --> 16:31.805
When he said it,
I believed it.

16:31.899 --> 16:33.232
<i> ♪ </i>

16:33.401 --> 16:37.478
The thing is,
everyone had a crush on him,

16:37.572 --> 16:40.890
and he chose me.

16:40.908 --> 16:43.459
You know what that felt like
for me?

16:45.505 --> 16:50.157
And after that, we had this big
secret, which was really sexy.

16:50.176 --> 16:51.175
There would be
these little moments

16:51.327 --> 16:52.568
of eye contact
in the hallway,

16:52.661 --> 16:56.163
and I just felt like
the hottest girl in school.

16:56.182 --> 16:57.348
And then when I got pregnant,

16:57.500 --> 17:01.577
he told me never
to tell anyone it was his.

17:01.596 --> 17:04.522
<i> ♪ </i>

17:04.749 --> 17:08.918
He didn't want to have anything
to do with me.

17:09.011 --> 17:10.753
Or Sam.

17:10.772 --> 17:12.772
<i> ♪ </i>

17:12.866 --> 17:14.774
Gabby, I'm so sorry.

17:14.868 --> 17:19.186
<i> ♪ </i>

17:19.280 --> 17:20.446
<i> (producers arguing)</i>

17:20.598 --> 17:21.947
NICK: Guys, shut up, shut up!
Come on.

17:22.042 --> 17:25.192
We need to get into
the minds of our demo.

17:25.286 --> 17:27.270
Jessica, your mom
just found out

17:27.288 --> 17:28.362
that Gabby slept with
her teacher in high school.

17:28.381 --> 17:29.363
Quick,
what does she think about it?

17:29.457 --> 17:30.606
My mom loves Gabby.

17:30.699 --> 17:33.700
She wants to see redemption
and/or revenge.

17:33.720 --> 17:34.868
Great, love 'em both.

17:34.962 --> 17:36.370
Redemption and revenge.
Anybody else?

17:36.422 --> 17:37.947
Honestly, my mom probably
thinks that Gabby's a slut

17:38.116 --> 17:40.224
that brought this on herself,
and she's probably just looking

17:40.451 --> 17:42.301
for attention, and if she
kept her eyes on her hemline,

17:42.453 --> 17:43.803
none of this
would have happened.

17:43.955 --> 17:45.546
Yikes, Dante's mom.
She was a kid.

17:45.714 --> 17:47.231
-Hey, you asked.
-My mother wants to know

17:47.458 --> 17:49.125
why I haven't marched
down the hall

17:49.143 --> 17:50.810
and castrated him myself.

17:50.962 --> 17:52.219
(producers murmuring)

17:52.238 --> 17:56.574
PRODUCER: I think I like
the idea.

17:56.725 --> 17:57.909
Anybody else?

17:58.060 --> 18:01.821
I keep wondering,
why did he choose me?

18:01.915 --> 18:04.657
Out of everyone.

18:04.733 --> 18:06.066
Was it because he liked me,

18:06.235 --> 18:09.312
or was it because he knew
I wouldn't complain?

18:09.330 --> 18:11.905
Was I just that fat girl
who could keep a secret?

18:11.999 --> 18:13.257
You're being so mean
to yourself.

18:13.367 --> 18:15.718
You want to know
what the worst part is?

18:17.655 --> 18:19.263
I still like him.

18:19.415 --> 18:22.916
I still think about what it
would be like to be with him.

18:22.936 --> 18:24.268
Gabby.

18:24.420 --> 18:26.178
I wish I could have been there
for you through this.

18:26.272 --> 18:29.165
I wish I had told you before

18:29.258 --> 18:32.017
or told literally anyone,

18:32.170 --> 18:35.530
but I was ashamed.

18:37.508 --> 18:39.099
Because if there's
one thing I learned,

18:39.268 --> 18:40.934
it's that there is
something about me

18:40.954 --> 18:42.862
that needs to be kept secret.

18:42.956 --> 18:45.289
And part of me
still believes that.

18:45.441 --> 18:46.791
<i> JESSICA:</i>
<i> She's gonna get doxxed.</i>

18:46.942 --> 18:48.108
Do we care about that?

18:48.128 --> 18:49.460
Well, silence is the enemy,

18:49.612 --> 18:51.129
and if she does this,
she'll inspire others.

18:51.356 --> 18:52.964
That's a great point.
People love bravery.

18:53.115 --> 18:54.523
Where are we
on the MeToo backlash?

18:54.617 --> 18:56.134
It's over; we're now on
the backlash to the backlash.

18:56.285 --> 18:57.635
Okay.
What are we even talking about?

18:57.862 --> 19:00.880
All we have is one odd moment
at the end of an interview.

19:01.032 --> 19:02.423
-And Gabby quit the show.
-NICK: Okay.

19:02.475 --> 19:04.291
What we're talking about
is going after the guy, right?

19:04.385 --> 19:06.202
Put him in a room with me
and a camera.

19:06.295 --> 19:07.478
If we want him to talk,
I'll get him to talk.

19:07.630 --> 19:09.129
Okay, what if we do that,
and we get sued?

19:09.223 --> 19:10.648
By who, a Detroit
public schoolteacher? Come on.

19:10.799 --> 19:12.391
And what if we don't do it,
and then it comes out?

19:12.485 --> 19:15.044
Yes, the last thing I need is
Ronan Farrow asking questions

19:15.062 --> 19:16.395
about what we knew
and when we knew it.

19:16.489 --> 19:18.063
Yeah, and I'll fight
Ronan Farrow every day--

19:18.216 --> 19:20.307
The man still works here!

19:20.326 --> 19:23.977
Pro: we go after him,
he gets fired.

19:23.997 --> 19:25.997
I find this whole conversation
disgusting.

19:26.224 --> 19:29.892
Sure, yes, but should
we do it or not?

19:29.911 --> 19:31.985
It should be up to Gabby.

19:32.005 --> 19:36.248
<i> ♪ </i>

19:36.401 --> 19:38.918
We were babies
in high school.

19:39.070 --> 19:41.161
We ate Lucky Charms
with chocolate milk.

19:41.181 --> 19:42.346
We didn't know how to do taxes.

19:42.573 --> 19:44.998
We drew little doodles
on each other's shoes

19:45.018 --> 19:46.075
at lunchtime.

19:46.093 --> 19:49.094
I still don't
really get taxes.

19:49.247 --> 19:52.005
Look, I'm not gonna tell you
what to do about Mr. A.

19:52.083 --> 19:53.674
or the show,

19:53.693 --> 19:57.010
but I'm gonna ask you
to just forgive yourself,

19:57.030 --> 19:59.422
because it's not your fault.

19:59.440 --> 20:01.032
And I really don't want
to see this guy

20:01.183 --> 20:04.851
take dance away
from you again.

20:04.946 --> 20:06.871
I don't know what to do.

20:07.022 --> 20:09.765
That's okay.
Maybe we can take a baby step.

20:09.858 --> 20:13.044
You know, you choreographed
something incredible today.

20:13.195 --> 20:15.955
How about we go watch
those kids dance?

20:16.049 --> 20:17.882
How many weddings
have I referred you for?

20:18.033 --> 20:20.251
No, no.
How many funerals, Larry?

20:20.478 --> 20:22.445
Oh, okay, how about that
community theater production

20:22.463 --> 20:24.055
of<i> Carousel,</i> huh?
"You'll Never Walk Alone"?

20:24.206 --> 20:25.723
Well, I'm walking alone
right now.

20:25.950 --> 20:27.708
Larry, how could you do this?

20:27.727 --> 20:30.636
I don't--we're done.

20:30.730 --> 20:32.587
Ah!

20:32.640 --> 20:34.214
DANTE: Simon?

20:34.234 --> 20:39.979
Um... so my dove guy is having
an abscessed tooth removed,

20:40.073 --> 20:41.814
but you know what?
Not to worry.

20:41.966 --> 20:44.075
Everything else
is sailing along.

20:44.302 --> 20:46.077
I've arranged for the dancers
to arrive from the stages.

20:46.304 --> 20:47.245
They're learning
the choreo now.

20:47.472 --> 20:49.080
I've already cleared the song.

20:49.231 --> 20:50.990
The streamer cannons are
coming in an hour.

20:51.084 --> 20:52.324
Zoe Washington has no idea,

20:52.477 --> 20:55.253
but it's gonna be
the best day of her life.

20:55.329 --> 20:57.830
And the worst day of Larry's.

20:57.924 --> 20:59.148
How's it going?
I don't know.

20:59.166 --> 21:00.925
I know this all just
kinda seems like a lot.

21:01.076 --> 21:02.668
I mean,
what if you do all this,

21:02.762 --> 21:04.320
and then Zoe still says no?

21:04.413 --> 21:07.339
You think she's gonna say no?
She said she liked me.

21:07.492 --> 21:09.249
Well, how do you know
she meant it, hmm?

21:09.343 --> 21:11.160
Well, what if she changed
her mind and didn't tell you?

21:11.178 --> 21:12.511
And then when you told her
that you broke up with the girl

21:12.663 --> 21:15.014
that you were seeing,
she didn't seem to care,

21:15.166 --> 21:16.849
even though she's the one
that told her mom

21:17.001 --> 21:18.425
that she loved you.
What the...

21:18.444 --> 21:20.336
Zoe told her mom
she loved me?

21:20.429 --> 21:22.280
SIMON: Okay, Reggie, Reggie,
I know you're struggling,

21:22.431 --> 21:23.614
but you're freaking
him out, okay?

21:23.841 --> 21:25.265
So listen.

21:25.285 --> 21:27.009
Maybe we're just gonna focus
on somebody else's narrative.

21:27.178 --> 21:28.677
You might learn
something, okay?

21:28.696 --> 21:29.845
Yeah.

21:29.905 --> 21:31.347
Zoe's gonna say yes,
though, right?

21:31.365 --> 21:33.182
Yeah, absolutely.
I'm six for six on proposals.

21:33.275 --> 21:34.775
Now, I need your hat size.

21:34.794 --> 21:36.685
PAULA: Did you know
that every other producer

21:36.704 --> 21:37.853
is together right now,

21:37.946 --> 21:39.188
deciding the future
of the show,

21:39.206 --> 21:43.192
and I am stuck here
in detention with you?

21:43.194 --> 21:46.545
You should go.
I won't tell anybody.

21:46.714 --> 21:48.639
Shut up.

22:09.329 --> 22:12.571
<i> (Gnarls Barkley's "Run</i>
<i> (I'm a Natural Disaster)")</i>

22:12.665 --> 22:15.166
<i> ♪ </i>

22:15.317 --> 22:16.742
ALLY: Whoa, hey, hey!
Hey!

22:16.836 --> 22:18.894
<i> ♪ </i>

22:18.913 --> 22:22.581
-What are you doing?
-Ah!

22:22.675 --> 22:24.842
God, I hate dancers.

22:25.069 --> 22:26.752
Can you not...

22:26.846 --> 22:28.512
Whoa.
Hello!

22:28.739 --> 22:30.997
We do not have access
to that property or permission!

22:31.092 --> 22:32.908
Thank you.

22:32.927 --> 22:34.185
Hey--all right, take it easy.

22:34.412 --> 22:35.853
Oh, you can't get
on the tables!

22:35.930 --> 22:39.005
<i> ♪ </i>

22:39.025 --> 22:41.100
Whoa, we haven't--no,
we have a...

22:41.268 --> 22:43.510
TV show.
Save it for the camera.

22:43.588 --> 22:45.938
Okay, you know what?
Who are you trying to impress?

22:46.107 --> 22:48.090
It's just us!

22:48.109 --> 22:49.258
Seriously, what are you doing
right now?

22:49.351 --> 22:51.017
Doesn't even make sense.
You're just wasted.

22:51.112 --> 22:52.370
This is so annoying.

22:52.521 --> 22:54.538
Oh, look at me.
I have arms and legs.

22:54.690 --> 22:55.764
I can dance.

22:55.858 --> 22:58.692
That's really badass, actually.

22:58.711 --> 23:01.695
No, no, stop.
I can't.

23:01.789 --> 23:04.531
Okay, all right.

23:04.625 --> 23:07.033
<i> SINGER: ♪ No time</i>
<i> for question asking ♪</i>

23:07.053 --> 23:08.535
<i> ♪ Time is passing by,</i>
<i> all right ♪</i>

23:08.629 --> 23:10.129
<i> ♪ You can't win, child,</i>
<i> we've all tried to ♪</i>

23:10.223 --> 23:12.965
<i> ♪ You've been lied to </i>

23:13.117 --> 23:15.284
Hey!
Paula's in the wind!

23:15.453 --> 23:18.287
So exciting to finally meet
you two.

23:18.305 --> 23:21.473
How do you feel about your mom
being on the show?

23:21.567 --> 23:24.143
-Pretty embarrassed.
-Can we talk about the guitar?

23:24.295 --> 23:25.903
I don't think now is the time
to talk about the guitar.

23:26.054 --> 23:27.220
What guitar?

23:27.240 --> 23:29.389
Mom's selling
all of Dad's stuff.

23:29.409 --> 23:31.075
First, it was his Bulls jersey,

23:31.226 --> 23:33.226
then his ergonomic
office chair.

23:33.246 --> 23:34.912
And now it's his guitar.

23:35.063 --> 23:37.415
I mean, it's like
she's trying to erase him.

23:37.566 --> 23:39.065
I just think that,
if he wanted those things,

23:39.160 --> 23:40.233
he would have taken them
with him,

23:40.253 --> 23:41.477
so can we please get...

23:41.495 --> 23:42.903
-Why...
-Back to the interview?

23:42.997 --> 23:44.329
-Are you like this?
-Like what?

23:44.482 --> 23:46.406
SOPHIA: I mean,
the second that he left,

23:46.500 --> 23:48.333
you've turned
into this weird eBay robot.

23:48.502 --> 23:50.911
Have you even stopped
to be sad?

23:50.930 --> 23:52.655
That's a fair question, Julia.

23:52.673 --> 23:55.266
How do you feel about
your husband's absence?

23:55.493 --> 23:56.767
Whose side are you on, Wayne?

23:56.994 --> 23:58.418
I'm on the side of honesty.

23:58.438 --> 24:00.329
It sounds like your daughters
are looking

24:00.422 --> 24:02.731
for a real emotional connection
with you.

24:06.520 --> 24:09.338
Okay, well, the honest answer
is, I can't afford to be sad.

24:09.431 --> 24:12.616
Kevin left, and someone has to
be the adult, and that is me.

24:15.346 --> 24:17.029
-Olivia, sweetheart--
-No.

24:17.123 --> 24:18.497
-Please just do this interview.
-No.

24:20.960 --> 24:23.711
Got what you needed?
Great.

24:29.302 --> 24:31.710
Evan, we're five minutes
out, man. What's going on?

24:31.804 --> 24:33.028
I'm gonna make
a fool of myself.

24:33.047 --> 24:34.972
-What if she says no?
-Wait just a second.

24:35.199 --> 24:36.140
-Do you like this girl?
-Yeah.

24:36.291 --> 24:37.641
Do you think about her
all the time?

24:37.793 --> 24:39.310
Yeah, even in calculus.

24:39.479 --> 24:42.204
-And that's a thing because--
-I love calculus, yeah.

24:42.297 --> 24:43.481
Right, right, right,

24:43.632 --> 24:45.207
and would you do anything
to make her happy?

24:45.300 --> 24:46.875
-Yes.
-And does she love flash mobs?

24:46.894 --> 24:47.968
-I think so?
-And tap dancing.

24:47.987 --> 24:49.378
I guess?

24:49.396 --> 24:51.063
Then you gotta try, man.
Come on, you gotta try.

24:51.215 --> 24:52.898
Okay, okay.

24:52.992 --> 24:55.067
Now, come on, man.
Let's go!

24:55.161 --> 24:57.328
Come on!
Get your head in the game.

24:57.479 --> 25:00.981
So the scary bee is supposed
to represent Paula

25:01.000 --> 25:02.315
in some way, or--

25:02.335 --> 25:03.984
It's a murder hornet, Al,
and it's an inside joke

25:04.003 --> 25:05.503
between us,
and you know what?

25:05.730 --> 25:07.563
She's gonna love it.
Just trust me, all right?

25:07.614 --> 25:09.489
